is in the dope game.

14:48.596 --> 14:51.179
I don't want you with them.
Do you hear me?

14:51.266 --> 14:53.803
- Do you?
- Yes, ma'am.

14:53.893 --> 14:56.100
All right.

14:57.105 --> 15:00.018
Come on, y'all.
Come on.

15:13.621 --> 15:16.659
- Hey. Mike?
- Yeah.

15:16.749 --> 15:20.708
I'm Harry Belton. Your coach wanted me
to fly up here and see you play.

15:20.795 --> 15:24.208
You're pretty good.
You've got a lot of potential.

15:24.299 --> 15:26.882
Potential?
That's what you call it?

15:26.968 --> 15:29.050
Who is this?
Who are you?

15:29.137 --> 15:32.050
I'm Harry. Mike's coach wanted me
to see your brother play.

15:32.140 --> 15:34.802
We run a camp in the summer
for high-school players.

15:34.892 --> 15:37.725
Are your parents around? I'd like
to talk to them about Mike attending.

15:37.812 --> 15:40.554
- I'm his mama.
- Nice try though.

15:40.648 --> 15:43.390
Oh. Uh, Mrs. Brown--

15:43.484 --> 15:45.737
- Miss.
- Miss Brown,

15:45.820 --> 15:48.653
can I take you to lunch

15:48.740 --> 15:50.731
so we can talk about Mike?

15:50.825 --> 15:53.692
What? No. Look, mister,
I don't know where you're from,

15:53.786 --> 15:55.652
but what his coach
should've told you

15:55.747 --> 15:58.705
is that I don't want Mike to even
think about basketball until after

15:58.791 --> 16:01.909
he gets into college, which, judging by
his grades, might not even happen.

16:02.003 --> 16:05.166
I agree. Grades are important,
especially the way Mike plays.

16:05.256 --> 16:07.543
Whoa whoa, what's that
supposed to mean?

16:07.634 --> 16:09.671
It means you're talented,
but talent's not enough.

16:09.761 --> 16:11.593
You need the right attitude
plus skill.

16:11.679 --> 16:13.420
Look, man.
Hold on, I got skills.

16:13.514 --> 16:16.097
Watch your mouth.
You know what?

16:16.184 --> 16:18.050
The reason that coach sent
you over here by yourself

16:18.144 --> 16:19.805
is 'cause he knows
he don't do nothing

16:19.896 --> 16:22.763
but tell these boys in this neighborhood
that they can make it to the pros.

16:22.857 --> 16:24.598
And when they end up
with their hearts broken

16:24.692 --> 16:26.148
they walk around here
mad at the world.

16:26.235 --> 16:28.442
That ain't happening
to my son, okay?

16:28.529 --> 16:29.781
So you're gonna
have to excuse me.

16:29.864 --> 16:31.775
I've got too much on my mind
to deal with this.

16:31.866 --> 16:34.198
Come on, Michael.
Come on.

16:35.995 --> 16:38.657
Potential? Huh.

16:49.717 --> 16:51.583
Girl, you got my money?

16:51.678 --> 16:54.966
No, but I was just wondering
if you could keep her

16:55.056 --> 16:57.297
forjust a few hours
while I try and go get it?

16:57.392 --> 16:59.133
Girl, do you think I'm crazy?

16:59.227 --> 17:02.219
Now you got to pay your money
like all the other mothers in here.

17:03.231 --> 17:05.893
Okay. Thank you.

17:05.983 --> 17:08.974
- Come on.
- Come on in here.

17:13.407 --> 17:16.241
- You hungry?
- No, ma'am.

17:16.327 --> 17:18.864
Yes, you are. Quit lying.

17:18.954 --> 17:20.695
When you bring that baby,

17:20.790 --> 17:23.531
oh, she be starving,
so I know you must be too.

17:23.626 --> 17:25.742
