- kinda rough lately.
- Mm-hmm.

32:12.014 --> 32:14.346
Well, get up there.
Have a seat. Sit down, honey.

32:14.433 --> 32:16.265
- Take a load off.
- Come on.

32:16.351 --> 32:18.638
- Thank you.
- Here.

32:18.729 --> 32:21.346
Oh, thanks.

32:21.440 --> 32:25.058
I lost my job lately, but even
before then, it was-- it was--

32:25.152 --> 32:27.189
it was kinda tough.

32:27.279 --> 32:30.192
- God will make a way. Won't He, Sarah?
- Mm-hmm.

32:30.282 --> 32:32.023
Sure wanna believe that.

32:32.117 --> 32:36.076
You must believe it, baby,
and don't you be ashamed to speak out.

32:36.163 --> 32:38.404
We got your back.

32:38.498 --> 32:41.536
'Cause I remember when my
husband died, if it wasn't for family,

32:41.627 --> 32:44.164
I don't know how me and my two girls
would have made it.

32:44.254 --> 32:46.245
I don't have much family.

32:46.340 --> 32:49.423
- Where these kids' daddy at?
- They're not in our lives.

32:49.509 --> 32:51.921
- They?!
- Vera.

32:53.680 --> 32:55.546
- Yeah, they.
- As in...

32:55.641 --> 32:57.757
more than one?

32:57.851 --> 33:00.434
- Three.
- Vera.

33:00.520 --> 33:03.103
Stay out of her business.

33:03.190 --> 33:05.101
Well...

33:05.192 --> 33:08.105
I wasn't trying to get in her business.
I'm gonna help her out.

33:08.195 --> 33:10.277
Here, this should help
you get a little bit.

33:10.364 --> 33:13.732
- Uh, no no no. I can't take that.
- It's the South, baby.

33:13.825 --> 33:15.611
You can take it.
It'll help out a little bit.

33:15.702 --> 33:17.363
No no no, thank you.

33:19.206 --> 33:21.368
I'm gonna go
check on my kids.

33:25.212 --> 33:29.331
Vera! $10, Vera? $10!

33:29.424 --> 33:31.256
What is she gonna do
with $10, Vera?

33:31.343 --> 33:34.631
First of all, she gonna buy
that kid a box of perm.

33:34.721 --> 33:37.964
- You see that child's head?!
- She has dreads.

33:38.058 --> 33:40.470
Dreads.
Let me spell that for you:

33:40.560 --> 33:43.803
N-A-P-P-Y.
Pshh!

33:47.484 --> 33:49.145
Uh-oh, watch the tree.

33:49.236 --> 33:51.227
All right, this game's points.

33:52.698 --> 33:54.905
- Be nice to him. Don't be--
- Whoa whoa whoa.

33:54.991 --> 33:57.483
- Oh!
- Oooh!

33:57.577 --> 34:00.114
What happened?

34:00.205 --> 34:02.367
- Oh, I see what happened.
- Hey!

34:02.457 --> 34:04.664
- Did you win?
- You know it, Mama.

34:04.751 --> 34:06.128
Aw, that's my baby.

34:06.211 --> 34:07.713
You said you want some of this?

34:07.796 --> 34:10.504
I got on my clothes,
my basketball clothes. You ready?

34:10.590 --> 34:12.456
Come on.
Gimme the ball.

34:12.551 --> 34:15.509
You-- don't stand there
looking like you ain't never seen this.

34:15.594 --> 34:18.462
Come on.
You wanna play?

34:20.934 --> 34:22.174
Hey.

34:23.562 --> 34:24.677
Hey.

34:24.771 --> 34:27.012
Harry, Brenda;
Brenda, Harry.

34:27.107 --> 34:28.518
Harry's a friend of the family.

34:28.608 --> 34:30.474
- We met already.
- Oh yeah?

34:30.569 --> 34:32.775
In Chicago. She kicked me
out of her house...

34:32.862 --> 34:35.696
when I told her her son had
potential to play pro ball.

34:35.782 --> 34:37.523
And what, you didn't
believe him?

34:37.617 --> 34:39.574
If Harry says it's true,
then it's the truth.

34:39.661 --> 34:41.618
So, what, you decided
to stalk us?

34:41.705 --> 34:43.696
No.

34:43.790 --> 34:45.871
- This is where I live.
- What?

34:45.958 --> 34:47.699
Harry, you see him foul me?

34:47.793 --> 34:49.831
You fouled me. Didn't--
you seen him, Harry?

34:49.920 --> 34:51.422
He fouled me.
You hit me on the leg.

34:51.505 --> 34:53.417
Excuse me.
Let me go ref this game.

34:55.010 --> 34:56.216
Game point!

34:56.303 --> 34:58.385
I'd still like to take
you out to lunch.

34:58.472 --> 35:00.759
Dinner's ready, you guys.

35:00.849 --> 35:02.385
That's my cue.
I'm coming, Cora!

35:02.476 --> 35:04.262
Ooh.

35:06.313 --> 35:09.226
Michael, come on. It's time
for dinner. I need you to wash up.

35:09.316 --> 35:13.230
- All right.
- It was really good seeing you again.

35:14.488 --> 35:15.899
Harry.

35:15.989 --> 35:18.401
_ Huh?
_ Harry-

35:18.492 --> 35:20.824
Harry.

35:20.911 --> 35:23.243
Sly dog. Ha ha ha!

35:23.330 --> 35:25.492
- I'll talk to you after dinner.
- Whoa whoa whoa!

35:25.582 --> 35:26.993
Man, hey hey.

35:27.083 --> 35:29.415
You didn't hear that?

35:29.503 --> 35:31.995
What, is that your way of asking
to stay for dinner?

35:32.088 --> 35:34.796
- Why, thank you.
- Whoa whoa whoa.

35:36.510 --> 35:39.923
If you trying to holler at her, man, you
need to come out of that sweaty shirt.

35:40.013 --> 35:41.924
Right.

35:42.015 --> 35:44.222
- I'll be right back.
- All right.

35:44.309 --> 35:46.016
Hey, I'll save you a seat.

35:46.102 --> 35:49.390
- Hey, right next to her.
- All right.

35:49.481 --> 35:52.564
And that was when we all
cried like babies.

35:52.651 --> 35:54.858
You don't know how
to tell no stories.

35:54.945 --> 35:57.312
L.B., Vera, y'all remember when

35:57.405 --> 35:59.271
Daddy tried to teach us
how to swim?

35:59.366 --> 36:01.448
- No, I don't remember that.
- Oh, I remember.

36:01.535 --> 36:04.118
I remember it because it was
like it was yesterday.

36:04.204 --> 36:08.619
I remember it was
Christmas Eve, 19...

36:08.708 --> 36:09.743
1940-something,
whatever.

36:09.835 --> 36:11.451
I remember.

36:11.545 --> 36:13.286
Daddy said he couldn't get us
nothing for Christmas.

36:13.380 --> 36:15.462
So he come in and he said,
"I'm gonna get the truck ready."

36:15.549 --> 36:17.756
- He loaded up horse on the truck.
- Uh-huh.

36:17.843 --> 36:19.459
You know, we ain't have
no engine in the truck.

36:19.553 --> 36:22.295
We just had a, you know,
old one-horsepower truck.

36:22.389 --> 36:23.754
- That was the horse.
- Giddy-up.

36:23.849 --> 36:25.305
Yeah, giddy-up, giddy-UP-

36:25.392 --> 36:28.680
We went down to that river.
I didn't want to jump in right off.

36:28.770 --> 36:30.602
That water was 50-below zero!

36:30.689 --> 36:32.600
<i>- Whoa'.
- Shdnufi.</i>

36:32.691 --> 36:35.558
Daddy got out there and he said,
"Get in the water!"

36:35.652 --> 36:37.814
And I said, "I ain't
getting in that water!"

36:37.904 --> 36:39.861
And he looked at me, he had
an extension cord in his hand.

36:39.948 --> 36:41.404
I didn't want to be no disobedient.

36:41.491 --> 36:44.108
So I got to that water
and I looked at it,

36:44.202 --> 36:47.661
and I teenched up there
and then I teeter-tottered.

36:47.747 --> 36:49.613
- Whoo.
- I teeter-tottered.

36:49.708 --> 36:52.325
Teeter-totter, next thing
you know...

36:52.419 --> 36:54.251
bang!

36:55.839 --> 36:58.331
I never learned to swim.

36:58.425 --> 37:01.042
I couldn't get the rhythm
of the stroke.

37:01.136 --> 37:04.128
Why is it that I felt
that I might choke?

37:04.222 --> 37:07.340
Mr. Brown is crazy.

37:07.434 --> 37:10.597
Harry, how is your mother?

37:10.687 --> 37:13.304
- She's good.
- Uh-huh.

37:13.398 --> 37:16.186
I'm glad she's good 'cause I know
she almost had a heart attack

37:16.276 --> 37:19.189
when she heard about all that trouble
you were in with all that illegal--

37:19.279 --> 37:20.861
Mama! Want some cake?

37:20.947 --> 37:22.858
Gimme the part
where they got that rum

37:22.949 --> 37:25.782
sopped up in there. Gimme that piece.
Gimme just that rum piece.

37:25.869 --> 37:27.359
I'm just glad to see you all right

37:27.454 --> 37:30.162
'cause I was praying for you.

37:30.248 --> 37:32.410
That prayer didn't get
no higher than the ceiling.

37:34.127 --> 37:36.710
- Mom.
- What, baby?

37:36.796 --> 37:39.083
- I got a tummy ache.
- Oh, honey,

37:39.174 --> 37:41.165
that's probably
because you ate too much.

37:41.259 --> 37:43.842
- Let me get you something.
- Don't worry about it, Ma.

37:43.929 --> 37:45.761
- I'll take care of her.
- Thank you.

37:45.847 --> 37:47.929
Young man, you know
where you going?

37:48.016 --> 37:50.007
Oh, yes, sir.
Excuse me a minute.

37:50.101 --> 37:52.058
Come on, Mike.

37:52.145 --> 37:53.510
All right. Night, baby.

37:53.605 --> 37:54.595
- Good night.
- Night.

37:54.689 --> 37:56.066
- Night.
- Later, Mike.

37:56.149 --> 37:59.232
Brenda, he seems like
such a nice young man.

37:59.319 --> 38:00.809
Thank you. He is.

38:00.904 --> 38:02.565
I couldn't make it without him.

38:02.656 --> 38:05.068
You know what? Now just a minute,
just a minute.

38:05.158 --> 38:09.117
I'm just curious. Anybody else at this
table want to know who this woman is?

38:09.204 --> 38:13.789
- Vera!
- All day y'all been skirting the issue.

38:13.875 --> 38:16.082
I want to know
who this woman is.

38:16.169 --> 38:18.752
- Mama--
- No no, uh uh uh uh!

38:18.838 --> 38:21.091
Who are you?

38:26.972 --> 38:28.679
Well, um...

38:28.765 --> 38:32.679
apparently Pop Brown
was my daddy.

38:32.769 --> 38:34.760
- What?
- Huh-uh, you's a liar.

38:34.854 --> 38:36.561
Apparently nothing.
You a liar!

38:36.648 --> 38:38.389
Huh-uh, the devil is a liar.

38:38.483 --> 38:41.942
Oh, hell to the no.
My daddy wasn't no rolling stone.

38:42.028 --> 38:43.689
Well, that's what
my mama said.

38:43.780 --> 38:46.442
- Who's your mama?
- Her name was Carol Cassidy.

38:46.533 --> 38:48.069
I don't know no Cassidy.
Who's that?

38:49.619 --> 38:51.451
I ain't got no reason
not to tell the truth.

38:51.538 --> 38:53.779
W-wait a minute.
I got something.

38:53.873 --> 38:56.205
Yeah, let's see what you got.

38:56.292 --> 38:58.545
Look at her.
She does lookjust like us.

38:58.628 --> 39:01.336
Look, I'm the baby of this family.
She ain't coming up in here.

39:01.423 --> 39:04.040
All that attitude and carrying on.
"We're from Chicago."

39:04.134 --> 39:05.795
What you got, girl?

39:05.885 --> 39:08.502
I got this letter and it
told me to come down here.

39:08.596 --> 39:10.883
Let me see this.
It's I.B.'s writing.

39:10.974 --> 39:13.056
- I.B., what the hell is this?
- I.B.?

39:13.143 --> 39:15.475
- What the hell is it?
- What's going on, I.B.?

39:15.562 --> 39:18.930
- Yeah, I.B., what's going on?
- I know all about this.

39:19.024 --> 39:21.732
Papa Brown been talking
to you about her?

39:21.818 --> 39:24.105
Yes, her and her mother.

39:24.195 --> 39:26.277
You see, when Pop Brown
got real sick,

39:26.364 --> 39:30.028
he started to tell me everything
about his past life.

39:30.118 --> 39:34.112
You know, before he got saved
and became a deacon.

39:34.205 --> 39:35.991
So you mean to tell me--

39:36.082 --> 39:38.119
you have a sister?

39:38.209 --> 39:40.120
Yep, and her mother

39:40.211 --> 39:42.589
was the love of his life
in Chicago.

39:42.672 --> 39:44.254
Oh, really?

39:44.340 --> 39:46.502
- Mm-hmm, yeah.
- Huh-uh-uh!

39:46.593 --> 39:48.755
'Cause I don't agree.
What are you saying?

39:48.845 --> 39:51.382
You see, when Pop Brown
was in Chicago,

39:51.473 --> 39:53.089
he was a pimp.

39:53.183 --> 39:56.141
And her mother was
his bottom ho.

39:56.227 --> 39:58.559
You don't talk
about my daddy.

39:58.646 --> 40:00.853
Hell to the no,
this is blasphemy.

40:00.940 --> 40:04.308
L.B., you don't talk about my daddy
like this, not at the dinner table.

40:04.402 --> 40:07.940
- Our daddy was a saint.
- Your daddy was a pimp!

40:09.699 --> 40:13.033
He was not a pim-- my daddy
used to date nice women.

40:13.119 --> 40:15.076
- Remember sweet Sadie?
- Yes.

40:15.163 --> 40:17.746
- Good girl.
- She was one of his whores.

40:17.832 --> 40:21.245
- Ho ho.
- What about Agnes with the freckles?

40:21.336 --> 40:23.247
She was a good girl-- Agnes.

40:25.131 --> 40:26.713
Freckle-faced ho.

40:26.800 --> 40:28.711
What about Arnette?

40:30.053 --> 40:33.296
- Latin ho.
- What about Tommy Lee?

40:34.474 --> 40:36.841
- Backdoor whore.
- What about Shirley?

40:36.935 --> 40:39.643
Shirley, the one that used to make
cupcakes for me when I was a child.

40:39.729 --> 40:42.437
Please don't tell me Shirley was no ho.
What about Shirley?

40:42.524 --> 40:45.312
- City ho.
- Miss Edna?

40:45.401 --> 40:47.859
She's a double ho.

40:47.946 --> 40:51.064
What about I.B. mama?

40:53.952 --> 40:55.238
L.B.?

40:55.328 --> 40:59.492
Nasty ho.

40:59.582 --> 41:01.994
Ain't nothing going
on here but the truth.

41:05.922 --> 41:08.459
Brenda, you sure you okay?

41:08.550 --> 41:10.211
Oh yeah. I'll be fine.

41:10.301 --> 41:12.554
But it's a good thing
this funeral's tomorrow

41:12.637 --> 41:16.175
- so I can get out of here.
- Let me welcome you to the Brown family.

41:16.266 --> 41:20.430
- Some welcome.
- I know it.

41:20.520 --> 41:22.807
This is getting pretty full.
I should take it out.

41:22.897 --> 41:24.604
Oh, okay. You sure
you want to do that?

41:24.691 --> 41:26.853
- Yeah, where?
- Just take it right out front.

41:31.030 --> 41:33.442
Ladies, I'm gonna say
good night.

41:33.533 --> 41:36.651
- Well, good night.
- Nice meeting you.

41:36.744 --> 41:39.156
Nice meeting you too.

41:45.378 --> 41:47.710
- Hey, let me help you with that.
- Oh, I got it.

41:47.797 --> 41:50.505
Around here men do that.

41:50.592 --> 41:53.050
Where I'm from women do it all.

41:57.724 --> 42:00.056
Well, then maybe
you should live here.

42:00.143 --> 42:02.054
God forbid.

42:02.145 --> 42:05.308
What?
What's wrong with my town?

42:05.398 --> 42:08.686
- You call this a town?
- Yeah.

42:08.776 --> 42:11.188
It's calming.

42:11.279 --> 42:12.895
It's too quiet here.

42:12.989 --> 42:15.777
Then maybe you should let me
show you how great a town it is.

42:15.867 --> 42:19.701
You know, I'm here for my father's funeral
and you're flirting with me.

42:19.787 --> 42:21.949
That is in poor taste.

42:22.040 --> 42:24.202
- Yeah.
- I'm sorry.

42:26.127 --> 42:28.209
Good night.

42:28.296 --> 42:30.037
Good night.

42:45.563 --> 42:49.522
Well, we are here today to say

42:49.609 --> 42:52.522
- goodbye...
- Lord, that's my daddy!

42:52.612 --> 42:54.523
...to one of our dear
beloved sons.

42:54.614 --> 42:56.605
Daddy, you should've
let me go with you!

42:56.699 --> 42:58.360
Daddy!

42:58.451 --> 43:01.785
Mom, Mom, take it easy.
Sit down, Mom.

43:01.871 --> 43:03.828
And I need you to understand

43:03.915 --> 43:07.579
that God will see you
through all this, sister.

43:10.630 --> 43:12.667
What the hell does
he got on his head?

43:12.757 --> 43:16.216
- And you must realize that...
- Monster, Mama, monster.

43:16.302 --> 43:19.636
- Baby, it's all right.
- ...in this hour of bereavement,

43:19.722 --> 43:23.056
there is such
a word as comfort.

43:23.142 --> 43:25.930
Yeah, Southern Comfort!
Yes, sir!

43:26.020 --> 43:28.682
- Hmph
- And God is faithful

43:28.773 --> 43:32.482
- to do exactly what he says he's gonna do.
- Preacher? Excuse me, Pastor?

43:32.568 --> 43:34.980
He do, He do!

43:35.071 --> 43:36.232
Psst!

43:36.322 --> 43:38.063
- Put me on the program.

43:38.157 --> 43:40.239
I wanted to say something
about my daddy.

43:40.326 --> 43:43.068
- Don't, please.
- You can put me on program.

43:43.162 --> 43:44.903
I'm trying to do
the sermon, please.

43:44.998 --> 43:47.911
- I'm preaching right now.
- You ain't doing no--

43:48.001 --> 43:50.459
you ain't doing no good job.
You're boring everybody.

43:50.545 --> 43:53.162
Look at my daddy's face.

43:54.882 --> 43:57.965
Deacon, he dead.

43:58.052 --> 44:00.544
- Put me on the program.
- I need to finish my sermon.

44:00.638 --> 44:02.754
- Remember that--
- Psst!

44:02.849 --> 44:05.466
You can let me say something
about my daddy. He my daddy.

44:05.560 --> 44:08.222
- Is he your daddy? Act like he your daddy.
- All right.

44:08.313 --> 44:10.429
- Just put me on the program.
- Come on.

44:10.523 --> 44:12.355
- Oh, Daddy!
- All right.

44:12.442 --> 44:14.729
Now I have more to say,
but right now

44:14.819 --> 44:16.901
his son Leroy Brown

44:16.988 --> 44:19.446
has a few words
that he wants to say.

44:19.532 --> 44:22.115
Leroy Brown, come on
and say something

44:22.201 --> 44:23.453
right up on that.

44:23.536 --> 44:25.152
- Me?
- Oh yes.

44:25.246 --> 44:27.157
- What?
- Let's go. Come on now.

44:27.248 --> 44:29.580
- Shut your mouth. Is he sure?
- Yes, Deacon.

44:29.667 --> 44:32.204
- They want me to say something?
- Come on up here, Deacon.

44:32.295 --> 44:33.535
I don't know what to say.

44:33.629 --> 44:35.290
You want me to say
something, I.B.?

44:35.381 --> 44:37.873
- Till we all dead.
- Okay.

44:37.967 --> 44:40.208
I'm "nerveless."

44:40.303 --> 44:43.921
I didn't plan on saying
nothing today.

44:44.015 --> 44:47.804
I just was in my room and I
jotted down a few things.

44:47.894 --> 44:50.636
- Can y'all hear me?
- Go on, Brown. Go on, baby.

44:50.730 --> 44:53.472
Is this on?

44:53.566 --> 44:55.148
It's on.

44:55.234 --> 44:58.818
I didn't plan on saying nothing.
Let the church say "amend."

44:58.905 --> 45:03.149
- Amen.
- Let the church say "amend" again.

45:03.242 --> 45:04.824
Amen.

45:04.911 --> 45:08.825
I want to let everybody know
today that Daddy died happy.

45:08.915 --> 45:11.953
He was happy...
I'm gonna miss my daddy.

45:12.043 --> 45:13.659
Bye-bye, Daddy.

45:13.753 --> 45:15.619
My daddy loved his people...

45:15.755 --> 45:19.669
I'm getting sick of this. It don't take nobody
that long to put nobody in the ground.

45:19.759 --> 45:22.592
- Stay calm, stay calm.
- I am calm. I'm just sick of it.

45:22.678 --> 45:25.670
He'll always be right here, y'all,

45:25.765 --> 45:27.221
right here in my heart.

45:27.308 --> 45:30.801
And I won't chatter no--
this ain't no funeral.

45:30.895 --> 45:33.102
- This is a "celebrate."
- Yeah!

45:33.189 --> 45:35.601
And we here to celebrate Daddy.

45:35.691 --> 45:37.853
And I'm telling y'all today,

45:37.944 --> 45:40.811
- my daddy was a happy man.
- Sit down!

45:40.905 --> 45:43.146
- That's what we need--
- Sit down, Brown!

45:43.241 --> 45:46.029
--More superheroes in this church.
We need peoples

45:46.119 --> 45:48.486
that'll stand up and be
heroes for the Lord.

45:48.579 --> 45:51.287
- That's enough.
- Show him, baby.

45:52.625 --> 45:54.536
Oh God.

45:54.627 --> 45:56.959
I gotta stop smoking.

45:57.046 --> 46:00.459
♪ Amazing ♪

46:00.550 --> 46:03.884
♪ Gra-a-a-ace ♪

46:03.970 --> 46:07.179
♪ How sweet, yes ♪

46:07.265 --> 46:09.506
♪ The sound... ♪

46:09.600 --> 46:12.638
One more time, Sarah.
She got one more time.

46:12.728 --> 46:16.187
Jesus, why?
Tell me why?

46:16.274 --> 46:19.983
That's it. Vera's really getting
on my nerves.

46:20.069 --> 46:22.902
♪ That saves... ♪

46:22.989 --> 46:28.359
♪ A wre-eeee-etch ♪

46:28.453 --> 46:32.117
♪ Like me-eee-- ♪

46:35.293 --> 46:37.705
- Uncle I.B.!
- I.B., what's wrong with you?

46:37.795 --> 46:40.082
You wanna go with her?
There's room for you too, you know?

46:40.173 --> 46:41.834
I'll wait.

46:43.468 --> 46:46.961
I'm the baby of this family
and I deserve some respect.

46:47.054 --> 46:49.432
- Right.
- I.B. pushed me in that grave.

46:49.515 --> 46:50.926
I know, Mama. I know.

46:51.017 --> 46:53.133
Everybody's act a fool.

46:53.227 --> 46:56.185
Should have let them put the dirt
on you too-- acting a damn fool.

46:56.272 --> 46:58.604
- Calm down, everybody.
- That's just crazy!

46:58.691 --> 46:59.931
Uh, hey, y'all.

47:00.026 --> 47:02.267
It was nice meeting
all of you, but, um...

47:02.361 --> 47:04.227
- I think we're gonna go now.
- Oh no.

47:04.322 --> 47:07.860
You have to stay till tomorrow
for the reading of the will.

47:07.950 --> 47:10.658
- Yeah.
- No! Daddy ain't left her nothing.

47:12.663 --> 47:15.781
No, um, I really think
we ought to be going.

47:15.875 --> 47:17.912
You can't leave, baby,

47:18.002 --> 47:21.290
'cause... the bus only
come every three days.

47:21.380 --> 47:24.293
- It'll be here tomorrow.
- Tomorrow, what?

47:24.383 --> 47:26.966
- It'll be okay.
- No no!

47:27.053 --> 47:29.340
I gotta go.
I-- no--

47:29.430 --> 47:31.512
You know what?
You know what I'm gonna do?

47:31.599 --> 47:34.261
I'm gonna go change and I'm gonna
be back in 15 minutes.

47:34.352 --> 47:36.309
I'm gonna take you
and your kids

47:36.395 --> 47:38.727
to see my town.

47:41.734 --> 47:43.270
Ah-- you'll like it.

47:43.361 --> 47:46.524
- I promise.
- Okay okay okay.

47:46.614 --> 47:48.855
- Okay, all right. Okay, all right.
- 15 minutes.

47:48.950 --> 47:51.408
- All right.
- Oh my God.

47:51.494 --> 47:54.532
All right, you know
I don't know you that well,

47:54.622 --> 47:57.205
but you'd better
watch out for him. Pshaw!

47:57.291 --> 47:59.828
Flashing that pretty smile...

47:59.919 --> 48:02.331
and that nickel-slick talk.

48:02.421 --> 48:06.039
He done broke a lot of women's hearts
out here in these backwoods.

48:08.469 --> 48:11.006
You be careful... sister.

48:11.097 --> 48:13.634
Brenda.

48:13.724 --> 48:16.557
- Brown, where you all at?
- We over here.

48:16.644 --> 48:18.851
Where that money
you owe me?

48:20.273 --> 48:21.763
- I'm gonna give you two.
- Thank you.

48:21.857 --> 48:24.144
Thank you. Gracias.

48:24.235 --> 48:26.351
You didn't know
I spoke Spanish, did you?

48:26.445 --> 48:28.698
Oooh, you should have
got one.

48:28.781 --> 48:30.488
See, it's not so bad.

48:31.534 --> 48:33.150
Hey, Harry.

48:35.413 --> 48:36.903
- Hey.
- Mmm.

48:36.998 --> 48:38.955
One of your women?

48:39.041 --> 48:41.703
- No, it's my cousin.
- Oh.

48:41.794 --> 48:44.752
That don't mean nothing
down here, do it?

48:45.965 --> 48:47.956
Oh ho.

48:48.050 --> 48:50.132
That's cold.

48:50.219 --> 48:53.211
I'm kidding.

48:53.306 --> 48:55.889
_ Hi!
_ Hi!

48:55.975 --> 48:58.888
Hi, baby! Oh.

48:58.978 --> 49:00.685
They're having fun.

49:00.771 --> 49:03.183
Yeah.

49:05.943 --> 49:08.230
Why don't you have
a woman, anyway?

49:08.321 --> 49:10.983
- Huh?
- I'm divorced.

49:11.073 --> 49:12.984
Ooooh.

49:13.075 --> 49:15.533
Six years, three kids

49:15.620 --> 49:17.611
and a whole lot of drama.

49:17.705 --> 49:19.742
My drama trumps your drama.

49:26.255 --> 49:28.713
Hey, step right up,
step right up.

49:28.799 --> 49:31.882
Who can get the ball in the basket?
How about you, young man?

49:31.969 --> 49:33.801
- Huh huh?
- Hey, Harry?

49:33.888 --> 49:35.470
Yeah, you there, sir.

49:37.558 --> 49:39.174
Get the ball in the basket,

49:39.268 --> 49:41.976
you can win a cute little doll
for the lovely lady back there.

49:42.063 --> 49:44.976
- Maybe you're scared.
- You got some money?

49:45.066 --> 49:48.229
The young man's going to clean
me out of all my profits.

49:48.319 --> 49:50.981
I'm in, but I'll just play.
Not for money.

49:52.198 --> 49:54.189
- Run it.
- How about every one we win

49:54.283 --> 49:55.614
you buy back from us?

49:55.701 --> 49:57.908
All right.

49:59.080 --> 50:01.412
Keep that elbow in, all right?

50:02.500 --> 50:03.865
That's what I'm talking, dawg.

50:03.959 --> 50:06.246
- Bing bing bing.
- Oh ho ho!

50:06.337 --> 50:07.623
That's good form.

50:07.713 --> 50:10.125
That's the difference
right there, man.

50:10.216 --> 50:12.127
Come on, man, get some more,
get some more animals, man...

50:12.218 --> 50:15.256
- Oh, man, look at you.
- Too easy.

50:19.809 --> 50:22.642
- Tosha, take this in the house for Mama.
- Okay.

50:22.728 --> 50:24.719
Hey, wait up.

50:30.152 --> 50:32.814
Hey, man, here's your cut.

50:32.905 --> 50:35.397
Oh no, you keep it.

50:37.868 --> 50:39.984
Thanks.

50:44.458 --> 50:46.415
Think I'm winning him over.

50:46.502 --> 50:48.994
Don't be so sure about that.

50:51.048 --> 50:54.507
He hasn't really had
a real man in his life.

50:54.593 --> 50:57.426
And I sure can't afford
to let another one come running in

50:57.513 --> 50:59.550
and out of it.

51:04.895 --> 51:08.479
Is it his life or your life
we're talking about?

51:08.566 --> 51:10.227
What?

51:10.317 --> 51:12.729
I don't know who
you're protecting, you or him.

51:15.614 --> 51:18.572
Both of us, I guess.

51:21.412 --> 51:22.868
I see.

51:22.955 --> 51:25.287
You really think
he's that good?

51:27.752 --> 51:29.163
I do.

51:29.253 --> 51:32.712
Well, how would that work?
I mean, how would you coach him?

51:32.798 --> 51:35.210
I mean, you're here.
He's with me in Chicago.

51:35.301 --> 51:37.793
And look, he's not
moving down here.

51:37.887 --> 51:39.719
I can make a few trips up there,

51:39.805 --> 51:42.137
give him some drills.

51:42.224 --> 51:44.761
Maybe in the summer,
he can do a camp

51:44.852 --> 51:47.059
with me and some
of the other players.

51:47.146 --> 51:50.980
Hmm, what about
his education?

51:51.066 --> 51:52.602
I promise you

51:52.693 --> 51:56.152
he'll come back
smarter than he left.

51:58.949 --> 52:02.738
Yeah, well, I'll think about it.

52:02.828 --> 52:05.035
- Take your time.
- I have to ask him.

52:05.122 --> 52:08.114
Yeah, do that.

52:10.169 --> 52:12.001
Hey, thank you for the day.

52:12.087 --> 52:14.044
I really appreciate it.

52:14.131 --> 52:16.748
No, thank you.

52:16.842 --> 52:17.957
Goodbye...

52:18.052 --> 52:21.044
and thank you
so much, Harry.

52:22.681 --> 52:24.672
Goodbye.

52:28.771 --> 52:30.762
Oh.

52:39.114 --> 52:41.367
It's for you.

52:44.829 --> 52:47.617
Thanks.

53:02.221 --> 53:04.383
Excuse me.

53:05.724 --> 53:08.056
I'm just gonna go and pack.

53:08.143 --> 53:10.054
No, you are gonna stay

53:10.145 --> 53:12.273
for the reading
of the will, aren't you?

53:12.356 --> 53:15.314
Oh, no no no no.

53:15.401 --> 53:18.143
Stay? Daddy didn't
leave her nothing.

53:18.237 --> 53:20.478
- Vera.
- You should stay.

53:20.573 --> 53:22.484
- No, really.
- Come on.

53:22.575 --> 53:24.407
Come on, sit down.

53:24.493 --> 53:26.825
- Come on over here.
- He your daddy too.

53:26.912 --> 53:29.825
Brenda, come on.

53:29.915 --> 53:31.497
Come on.
Come on in here now.

53:31.584 --> 53:33.450
Come on, you'll probably
thank me too.

53:33.544 --> 53:35.205
You're Daddy's child,
you may as well.

53:35.296 --> 53:36.957
- You never know.
- Why don't you shut--

53:37.047 --> 53:38.458
Sit down now, sit sit.

53:38.549 --> 53:39.835
L.B., she ain't no puppy-

53:39.925 --> 53:41.836
What, you gonna have
her sit and do tricks?

53:41.927 --> 53:44.464
Brother Sam, you read
the last will and "testicles."

53:44.555 --> 53:47.343
Yeah, that's what
I've been waiting for.

53:47.433 --> 53:49.470
I got dressed up
for this. Come on.

53:49.560 --> 53:51.096
Okay, folks...

53:51.186 --> 53:53.928
Pop Brown's last
will and testament.

53:54.023 --> 53:56.105
Here it is.

53:56.191 --> 53:59.855
"To I.B. and his
beautiful wife Sarah..."

53:59.945 --> 54:02.983
Beautiful? Must have been blind,
crippled and crazy.

54:04.950 --> 54:06.987
Leave all my money..."

54:07.077 --> 54:09.569
<i>- Whoa'. Thank you , Daddy.
- Sweet'.!</i>

54:09.663 --> 54:14.373
- "...a total amount of $575."
- You rich! You rich!

54:14.460 --> 54:17.043
- That ain't nothing.
- What? 500?

54:17.129 --> 54:19.871
We-- we took care
of that sucker till he died.

54:19.965 --> 54:22.127
He just leave us
nothing but that?

54:22.217 --> 54:25.050
$575.

54:25.137 --> 54:28.050
I washed his toes
and cleaned his nose!

54:28.140 --> 54:30.723
He's so happy he can't
get his words out. He's rich.

54:30.809 --> 54:32.391
And and and--
keep reading, baby.

54:32.478 --> 54:34.890
- "To Vera..."
- Yes.

54:34.980 --> 54:37.893
Leave all my love."

54:37.983 --> 54:39.360
Love, yes, and...

54:39.443 --> 54:41.650
"May it keep you warm at night."

54:43.280 --> 54:45.191
There's got to be more.
You keep reading, baby.

54:45.282 --> 54:47.239
Keep reading 'cause I know
there's more for me.

54:47.326 --> 54:49.192
"And to Brown..."

54:49.286 --> 54:51.323
Oh, boy, this is good.

54:51.413 --> 54:53.529
Leave my house."

54:53.624 --> 54:55.410
The house?

54:55.501 --> 54:58.914
I'd rather have the love.
That house is tore up, Brown.

54:59.004 --> 55:01.086
Shut up, Vera.
We grew up in that house.

55:01.173 --> 55:04.006
Yeah, us and several families

55:04.093 --> 55:06.755
of rats and roaches.
What the hell is that?

55:06.845 --> 55:09.177
"To my daughter Brenda..."

55:09.264 --> 55:10.925
- Brenda?
- Brenda?

55:11.016 --> 55:14.805
<i>_</i> wh__
- leave my old rental property."

55:14.895 --> 55:18.388
Oh, Brenda,
that's wonderful.

55:18.482 --> 55:20.814
He left me a house?

55:51.932 --> 55:54.765
Do you think we're living here?

55:54.852 --> 55:57.139
Do you think
we're living here now?

55:57.229 --> 56:00.847
Okay, well, it has potential.

56:00.941 --> 56:03.979
Potential to be torn down.

56:04.069 --> 56:05.810
Is this our house, Mama?

56:05.904 --> 56:07.815
Looks that way, baby.

56:07.906 --> 56:10.398
- I'm gonna go back to the projects.
- Yeah, me too.

56:10.492 --> 56:12.074
Me three.

56:14.038 --> 56:16.370
I'd stay with you, brother.

56:21.086 --> 56:23.077
Hmm.

56:31.513 --> 56:33.595
Come on.

56:33.682 --> 56:35.673
At least go inside.

56:36.977 --> 56:38.638
All right, but, Tosha, Lena,

56:38.729 --> 56:41.096
y'all wait in the car.
Come on, go ahead.

56:41.190 --> 56:43.181
Looks dangerous in here.

56:46.612 --> 56:48.319
Ma.

56:50.240 --> 56:52.231
It got a welcome mat.

56:59.041 --> 57:01.032
Ooh.

57:05.380 --> 57:07.997
- It's a nice house.
- Really?

57:08.092 --> 57:10.459
What you looking at?

57:12.429 --> 57:14.340
It just needs a little work.

57:14.431 --> 57:16.889
This house don't need
no little nothing.

57:16.975 --> 57:19.057
- Ma, come on.
- What?

57:19.144 --> 57:21.055
Can we please get out of here?

57:21.146 --> 57:22.728
I'm not trying to miss the bus.

57:22.815 --> 57:26.024
Could you just give me a minute?
Let me ask you something.

57:26.110 --> 57:28.977
What do you think about
Harry coaching you?

57:29.071 --> 57:32.314
- Hmm?
- I'm cool with it if it gets us out of here.

57:33.951 --> 57:36.739
Oh, he cool with it.

57:36.829 --> 57:38.240
That's good.

57:38.330 --> 57:40.913
Uh-huh.

57:40.999 --> 57:44.242
You know, I really wish
you weren't leaving.

57:44.336 --> 57:47.795
Well, gotta get back to my life.

57:47.881 --> 57:50.794
- Ma, come on!
- I'm coming.

57:56.098 --> 57:58.055
Brenda, you leaving
me so soon?

57:58.142 --> 58:00.383
Yeah, we got to be heading back.

58:00.477 --> 58:02.343
Okay, well, look,
here's my number.

58:02.437 --> 58:04.144
I want you to keep in touch, okay?

58:04.231 --> 58:07.098
- Oh, I will.
- All right.

58:07.192 --> 58:08.728
And here...

58:08.819 --> 58:11.186
What's this?

58:11.280 --> 58:14.113
It's from me and Sarah.
We wanted to bless you with something.

58:14.199 --> 58:16.315
No, Cora, no. No, I can't.

58:16.410 --> 58:18.651
- No, take it.
- I can't.

58:18.745 --> 58:21.157
You have to take it.
We wanted to bless you with it.

58:21.248 --> 58:23.285
It's just a little something.
Brenda, please.

58:23.375 --> 58:25.582
Ain't no telling when
I'd be able to pay y'all back.

58:25.669 --> 58:27.626
Oh, honey,
don't worry about that.

58:27.713 --> 58:30.000
If some of these fathers
don't take care of these babies,

58:30.090 --> 58:33.048
then us single mothers have
to stick together. Please take it.

58:35.345 --> 58:38.383
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

58:38.473 --> 58:41.465
This is the nicest thing
that anybody's ever done for me.

58:41.560 --> 58:43.551
- Really?
- Yeah.

58:43.645 --> 58:45.852
Well, maybe you need
to change your friends.

58:48.233 --> 58:51.726
- Thank you, thank you.
- Oh, you're so welcome.

59:01.038 --> 59:03.621
- What did he say?
- Yeah, he hiring all right,

59:03.707 --> 59:05.618
but not for the job
he advertising for.

59:05.709 --> 59:08.076
- I go kill him now.
- No no no no.

59:08.170 --> 59:10.286
- Cheryl.
- Let me go.

59:10.380 --> 59:12.997
Stop it, calm down.

59:13.091 --> 59:16.880
Hey, don't you wanna
hear about my trip, huh?

59:16.970 --> 59:19.883
- You never told me about the trip.
- Don't ask.

59:19.973 --> 59:22.465
- Brenda, you just--
- I'm just kidding.

59:22.559 --> 59:24.596
Did he leave you
anything at least?

59:24.686 --> 59:27.144
Yeah, a house.

59:27.231 --> 59:29.689
- When are we moving?
- Huh-uh, girl, it's so raggedy.

59:29.775 --> 59:32.483
You can't live in it.
Compared to that, we live in a palace.

59:32.569 --> 59:34.151
Brenda, don't be selfish.

59:34.238 --> 59:36.229
Let's move to Georgia
so I can find me one

59:36.323 --> 59:39.406
of those big old
Jethro-looking papis

59:39.493 --> 59:42.485
so I can cucuchanga.

59:42.579 --> 59:45.492
Girl, you know what?
I think I might have met somebody

59:45.582 --> 59:47.493
- who'd be just your style.
- For me?

59:47.584 --> 59:48.790
Uh-huh.

59:48.877 --> 59:50.868
His name's Brown.

59:54.549 --> 59:56.540
I got it.

59:56.635 --> 59:59.468
Who is it?

59:59.554 --> 01:00:01.545
Hey.

01:00:01.640 --> 01:00:03.472
Hey.

01:00:05.143 --> 01:00:07.180
What you doing here?

01:00:07.271 --> 01:00:09.182
I've been thinking
about what you said,

01:00:09.273 --> 01:00:11.389
and I'm gonna help you out.

01:00:11.483 --> 01:00:14.566
So can I come in,

01:00:14.653 --> 01:00:16.644
Please?

01:00:19.825 --> 01:00:22.567
Yeah.

01:00:22.661 --> 01:00:24.652
Come on in.

01:00:36.842 --> 01:00:39.834
Damn, girl, this how you live?

01:00:41.305 --> 01:00:43.546
You gonna give me
some money or not?

01:00:43.640 --> 01:00:46.348
What you gonna give me, huh?

01:00:46.435 --> 01:00:49.427
I ain't gonna
give you nothing.

01:00:49.521 --> 01:00:53.014
- Aw, come on, girl, damn it.
- No, stop it, stop it.

01:00:53.108 --> 01:00:55.645
You oughta wanna do the right thing
and take care of your son.

01:00:55.736 --> 01:00:57.443
- You're right.
- Why I gotta threaten you

01:00:57.529 --> 01:00:59.270
with child support
to take care of him?

01:00:59.364 --> 01:01:00.946
Damn, Brenda, do it.

01:01:01.033 --> 01:01:04.571
- The boy probably ain't mine anyway.
- You bastard!

01:01:04.661 --> 01:01:06.163
You need this money,
don't you, right?

01:01:06.246 --> 01:01:07.862
So come on, baby,
where's the bedroom?

01:01:07.956 --> 01:01:10.789
No, stop it. I don't sleep
with men for money.

01:01:10.876 --> 01:01:14.119
Well, your mama used to,
didn't she?

01:01:14.212 --> 01:01:17.204
I ain't my mama. Get the hell
out of my house!

01:01:20.218 --> 01:01:23.461
Forget you then.
You all ain't getting nothing.

01:01:23.555 --> 01:01:25.842
I don't care if both of y'all
starve to death.

01:01:25.932 --> 01:01:29.220
You bastard. You would
do that to your own son?

01:01:29.311 --> 01:01:31.268
- Hey.
- You're just evil.

01:01:31.355 --> 01:01:34.814
I told you when you was pregnant I
didn't give a damn about you or the boy.

01:01:34.900 --> 01:01:38.313
Matter of fact, what did you do with
the $200 I gave you for the abortion?

01:01:38.403 --> 01:01:40.485
I'll bet you wish
you had that $200 now.

01:01:40.572 --> 01:01:43.064
- Don't you?
- Hey, Michael, baby.

01:01:44.409 --> 01:01:47.026
Hey, Mike. What's up, boy?

01:01:49.748 --> 01:01:51.989
Mama, why you begging like this?

01:01:52.084 --> 01:01:54.291
No no, he ain't gotta help us.

01:01:54.378 --> 01:01:56.460
No, I know how to make some things
happen on my own.

01:01:56.546 --> 01:01:58.332
You don't need
to beg this motherf--

01:01:58.423 --> 01:02:00.630
Leaveit
He's still your father.

01:02:00.717 --> 01:02:03.675
- Get your hand out of my face.
- Boy, better watch your mouth!

01:02:03.762 --> 01:02:06.675
- No, no, it's not worth it.
- Mama, are you defending him?

01:02:06.765 --> 01:02:09.302
Look, if you ain't
man enough to help us,

01:02:09.393 --> 01:02:12.431
I know how to make some things
happen on my own.

01:02:12.521 --> 01:02:14.979
- No, baby. Where are you going?
- No no.

01:02:15.065 --> 01:02:17.022
Michael! Mike, stop him.

01:02:17.109 --> 01:02:19.726
That boy ain't my responsibility.
It isn't my problem.

01:02:22.572 --> 01:02:26.065
No, Michael!

01:02:26.159 --> 01:02:28.070
Michael!

01:02:54.438 --> 01:02:55.849
Michael.

01:02:55.939 --> 01:02:57.725
. Hey-
. Hey-

01:02:57.816 --> 01:03:00.604
Can I come in?

01:03:00.694 --> 01:03:02.810
Yeah yeah, come on in.

01:03:10.162 --> 01:03:12.153
Have a seat.

01:03:14.416 --> 01:03:17.283
I'm sorry. I thought
you were Michael.

01:03:17.377 --> 01:03:20.244
He's not here?

01:03:20.338 --> 01:03:21.840
No.

01:03:21.923 --> 01:03:24.961
Did you tell him about the practice
sessions I set up for him?

01:03:25.051 --> 01:03:27.179
