- Thank you. Thank you.

01:19:07.618 --> 01:19:10.952
L-- I don't know what to say.

01:19:11.038 --> 01:19:12.870
Money shot.

01:19:12.957 --> 01:19:15.699
Here you go. Go up strong.
Always go up strong.

01:19:21.298 --> 01:19:24.711
You know, I think
that Harry's a nice man.

01:19:24.802 --> 01:19:26.463
- Yes, he is.
- Mm-hmm.

01:19:26.554 --> 01:19:30.013
- Thank you.
- He put up the most money for this house.

01:19:30.099 --> 01:19:31.885
- He sure did.
- He did?

01:19:31.976 --> 01:19:33.558
And I think he likes you.

01:19:33.644 --> 01:19:36.227
Mm-hmm.

01:19:36.313 --> 01:19:37.895
- Mama?
- Yeah, baby.

01:19:37.982 --> 01:19:39.598
Where do these
two lovebirds go?

01:19:39.692 --> 01:19:41.649
Come on, I'll show you.

01:19:46.157 --> 01:19:48.023
I think...

01:19:48.117 --> 01:19:50.154
he likes her son.

01:19:50.244 --> 01:19:51.734
What are you talking about?

01:19:51.829 --> 01:19:53.285
Honey, are you that naive?

01:19:53.372 --> 01:19:55.739
You haven't noticed all that attention
he been giving that boy?

01:19:55.833 --> 01:19:57.540
What are you trying to say, Vera?

01:19:57.626 --> 01:19:59.879
Oh, not like that.

01:19:59.962 --> 01:20:03.330
He's being so nice to her
because her son

01:20:03.424 --> 01:20:04.835
is a gold mine.

01:20:04.925 --> 01:20:06.791
Okay? He's trying to get in

01:20:06.886 --> 01:20:09.674
so he can get that boy to go pro
so he can get some of them perks...

01:20:10.973 --> 01:20:13.590
maybe pay off some of them
gambling debts, okay?

01:20:13.684 --> 01:20:17.894
Child, please.
This is an investment.

01:20:17.980 --> 01:20:19.687
She better watch out.

01:20:19.773 --> 01:20:21.935
- I don't believe none of that.
- Me neither.

01:20:22.026 --> 01:20:24.142
Why else would
a man be this nice

01:20:24.236 --> 01:20:25.977
to a woman with three--

01:20:26.071 --> 01:20:28.563
count 'em-- three kids.

01:20:28.657 --> 01:20:31.445
Well, you know, Vera, there are
some good men in this world.

01:20:31.535 --> 01:20:33.617
And Harry happens
to be one of them.

01:20:33.704 --> 01:20:36.787
- That's right.
- Not according to the local bookies.

01:20:36.874 --> 01:20:39.081
Why you think he got
kicked out of the league?

01:20:39.168 --> 01:20:42.206
Don't sit there acting like y'all don't
know this boy got a gambling problem.

01:20:42.296 --> 01:20:44.879
- Don't be acting like you don't know.
- You need to stop

01:20:44.965 --> 01:20:47.127
- listening to all that gossip, Vera.
- Please.

01:20:47.218 --> 01:20:50.677
- Stop being messy.
- Hush your mouth before she hears you.

01:20:50.763 --> 01:20:53.004
- Yes.
- If you ain't happy,

01:20:53.098 --> 01:20:55.260
you don't want nobody else to be.

01:20:55.351 --> 01:20:57.809
Well, I called it like
I see it and smell it!

01:20:57.895 --> 01:21:00.637
Well, you're always
smelling up some mess.

01:21:00.731 --> 01:21:02.313
That's right.

01:21:02.399 --> 01:21:04.652
Do your negative
smelling somewhere else

01:21:04.735 --> 01:21:06.646
'cause you're always
smelling up a mess.

01:21:11.242 --> 01:21:12.698
- Cora!
- What?

01:21:12.785 --> 01:21:14.492
- Cora!
- Yeah!

01:21:14.578 --> 01:21:17.320
I'm in the kitchen!
I'm in the kitchen!

01:21:17.414 --> 01:21:20.657
Your mama done went crazy!
People just everywhere!

01:21:20.751 --> 01:21:23.209
Mr. Brown, please!

01:21:23.295 --> 01:21:25.787
Cora, you slapped your daddy?
I oughta whup your butt.

01:21:25.881 --> 01:21:27.383
Calm down. What's wrong?

01:21:27.466 --> 01:21:28.877
Just sit down. Sit down.

01:21:28.968 --> 01:21:30.299
- Turn the TV on.
- Okay--

01:21:30.386 --> 01:21:32.127
- Turn the TV on!
- What happened on the TV?

01:21:32.221 --> 01:21:34.178
- Get the TV on.
- I'm trying to get it on. Hold on.

01:21:34.265 --> 01:21:36.176
- What happened?
- Look!

01:21:36.267 --> 01:21:39.976
A routine traffic stop turned
into one of the largest and most bizarre

01:21:40.062 --> 01:21:42.144
and shocking police pursuits

01:21:42.231 --> 01:21:44.347
that we have ever seen.

01:21:44.441 --> 01:21:47.274
This old woman is driving
like she has a lot to lose.

01:21:47.361 --> 01:21:49.318
Who could this be calling
me right now? Hello.

01:21:49.405 --> 01:21:52.193
Cora, hey.
How you doing, baby?

01:21:52.283 --> 01:21:53.990
Madea, please tell me
that's not you.

01:21:54.076 --> 01:21:55.487
Yeah, it's me, honey.

01:21:55.578 --> 01:21:56.784
Yeah.

01:21:56.870 --> 01:21:58.486
Madea, why don't you
just pull over?

01:21:58.581 --> 01:22:00.117
- You can't out--
- I can't pull over.

01:22:00.207 --> 01:22:02.164
- You goin' to jail.
- These police is after me.

01:22:02.251 --> 01:22:03.662
Hold on, I'm gonna put you
on speakerphone.

01:22:03.752 --> 01:22:05.459
Mabel, pull over. Just stop.

01:22:05.546 --> 01:22:08.083
Oh, Lordy, there's helicopters
and everything now.

01:22:08.173 --> 01:22:11.256
- Pull your car over--
- Mabel, you can't outrun

01:22:11.343 --> 01:22:13.334
- the "helichoppers."
- Please, Madea, please!

01:22:13.429 --> 01:22:16.171
- They ain't taking me to jail!
- Like hell they ain't.

01:22:16.265 --> 01:22:18.381
...just gonna send me to jail.
I'm going all the way this time.

01:22:18.475 --> 01:22:20.341
I'm going all the way this time.

01:22:20.436 --> 01:22:22.222
Madea, please
pull the car over.

01:22:22.313 --> 01:22:24.554
They ain't gonna get me!
They ain't gonna get me!

01:22:24.648 --> 01:22:26.355
I'm gonna be on "Cops."

01:22:26.442 --> 01:22:27.898
No, you can't. Madea, please.

01:22:27.985 --> 01:22:29.851
I love you, honey.
Please just pull over.

01:22:29.945 --> 01:22:31.527
I can't pull over, Cora.

01:22:31.614 --> 01:22:34.072
Y'all come down there to DeKalb County,
put $20 on my book.

01:22:34.158 --> 01:22:36.240
I'm running out of gas.
I might have to stop.

01:22:36.327 --> 01:22:39.319
If it's any "constipation,"
I love you.

01:22:39.413 --> 01:22:41.700
I always have
and I always will.

01:22:41.790 --> 01:22:43.747
Madea, please.
I love you, honey, please--

01:22:43.834 --> 01:22:45.745
Yeah, I love you too.
Go to hell.

01:22:48.672 --> 01:22:50.504
- Hey, Ma.
- Hey, sweetheart.

01:22:51.550 --> 01:22:53.291
- Guess what.
- What?

01:22:53.385 --> 01:22:55.672
Harry took me to his lawyer
to sign a contract with him.

01:22:55.763 --> 01:22:58.095
- He's my manager now.
- He did what?

01:22:58.182 --> 01:23:00.219
Yeah, I sent some
footage to a pro scout.

01:23:00.309 --> 01:23:02.175
I don't know
how the word got out,

01:23:02.269 --> 01:23:05.682
but next thing I know, there's bunch
of agents at the gym pressuring Mike.

01:23:05.773 --> 01:23:09.061
You know, I had him sign something--
so they wouldn't take advantage of him.

01:23:09.151 --> 01:23:12.610
- Harry knows his stuff, Mama.
- I know a little bit.

01:23:12.696 --> 01:23:14.937
Michael, why don't you
go check on your sisters,

01:23:15.032 --> 01:23:18.241
- make sure they wash up?
- Okay.

01:23:20.537 --> 01:23:22.494
- You okay?
- Yeah.

01:23:23.540 --> 01:23:25.952
You been awful quiet
the last few days.

01:23:26.043 --> 01:23:27.829
I'm fine.

01:23:27.920 --> 01:23:29.752
Harry, can I
ask you something?

01:23:29.838 --> 01:23:31.704
Yeah.

01:23:32.716 --> 01:23:35.549
What's in this for you?

01:23:35.636 --> 01:23:38.594
- What are you talking about?
- Why is he so important to you?

01:23:38.681 --> 01:23:41.139
- Hmm?

01:23:41.225 --> 01:23:43.512
- Hmm.
- Mike's a good kid.

01:23:43.602 --> 01:23:45.513
He's a talented kid.

01:23:47.231 --> 01:23:48.813
What are you
talking about?

01:23:50.776 --> 01:23:53.143
I don't like you spending
all this time with him.

01:23:53.237 --> 01:23:56.730
And I don't understand why you're
sending footage to pro scouts.

01:23:57.741 --> 01:23:59.323
Trying to-- trying to help.

01:23:59.410 --> 01:24:01.026
Why? Why? What for?

01:24:01.120 --> 01:24:02.610
What's in it for you?

01:24:02.705 --> 01:24:04.912
I mean, if he gets
a million-dollar contract,

01:24:04.998 --> 01:24:06.659
you think you
gonna get your cut?

01:24:06.750 --> 01:24:08.161
Is this some
kinda game to you?

01:24:08.252 --> 01:24:09.834
Whoa whoa whoa, hold on.

01:24:09.920 --> 01:24:12.958
Where is this coming from?

01:24:13.048 --> 01:24:16.006
Huh? What, have that many men hurt
you that you can't trust one?

01:24:16.093 --> 01:24:18.050
This ain't about me, all right?

01:24:18.137 --> 01:24:20.174
This is about you.

01:24:20.264 --> 01:24:22.255
Now, how much gambling
debt are you in?

01:24:22.349 --> 01:24:24.556
You didn't think
I'd hear about that?

01:24:31.775 --> 01:24:35.188
- You think I'm in it for some money?
- Well, are you?

01:24:35.279 --> 01:24:36.690
Is that what you think of me?

01:24:36.780 --> 01:24:39.522
Should that be
what I think of you?

01:24:39.616 --> 01:24:43.450
- Brenda--
- You're not going to be his manager.

01:24:45.789 --> 01:24:48.372
- Brenda--
- No, just go. Go. Go, please.

01:24:48.459 --> 01:24:52.999
I paid all of my gambling debts.
I don't owe anybody anything.

01:24:54.506 --> 01:24:56.463
Get out.

01:25:12.232 --> 01:25:14.223
Oh, hell. I'm running out of gas.

01:25:14.318 --> 01:25:16.184
Pull your car over to the side.

01:25:16.278 --> 01:25:18.645
Cora, here.

01:25:19.698 --> 01:25:22.736
Go bail your mama out.
Give her this $20.

01:25:22.826 --> 01:25:24.487
What-- what is this for?

01:25:24.578 --> 01:25:26.239
It's for back child support.

01:25:26.330 --> 01:25:27.991
Back--

01:25:28.081 --> 01:25:30.118
I owe it to ya.

01:25:30.209 --> 01:25:31.745
And there it is.

01:25:31.835 --> 01:25:34.167
- As fast as it started--
- Oh, they got her.

01:25:34.254 --> 01:25:35.665
But it still has gone down

01:25:35.756 --> 01:25:38.669
as one of the longest
police pursuits in history.

01:25:38.759 --> 01:25:41.296
What the hell? They gonna
send "helichoppers"

01:25:41.386 --> 01:25:43.343
and all these police cars
for a little old woman.

01:25:43.430 --> 01:25:46.263
- Get out of the vehicle now.
- Don't shoot.

01:25:46.350 --> 01:25:49.843
I'm getting out of the car.
They gonna lock your ass up.

01:25:51.688 --> 01:25:54.271
I ain't got no weapon.

01:25:54.358 --> 01:25:56.019
I ain't never do nothing wrong.

01:25:56.109 --> 01:25:58.362
- You gonna leave me up here--
- I ain't got no weapon.

01:25:58.445 --> 01:26:00.561
All of this for me, huh?

01:26:01.907 --> 01:26:04.194
What the hell you
got me surrounded for?

01:26:04.284 --> 01:26:07.117
She got a gun!
She-- she kidnapped me.

01:26:07.204 --> 01:26:10.492
Get out of your
vehicle with your hands up.

01:26:17.881 --> 01:26:19.713
Very slowly!
Very slowly!

01:26:23.011 --> 01:26:24.467
Put your hands
on the car, ma'am.

01:26:24.555 --> 01:26:26.262
- Hands on the car right now--
- Hold on one minute.

01:26:26.348 --> 01:26:28.589
- Let me tell you something here.
- Put your hands on the car.

01:26:28.684 --> 01:26:31.472
I ain't finna put my hands on the car
'cause my hands is hurtin'.

01:26:31.562 --> 01:26:33.303
- Ma'am, put your hands--
- Who the hell you talkin' to?

01:26:33.397 --> 01:26:35.138
- You don't want--
- Put your hands on the car!

01:26:35.232 --> 01:26:36.973
- You ain't gonna take me down!
- Settle down, ma'am!

01:26:37.067 --> 01:26:38.478
Put your hands on the car now.

01:26:38.569 --> 01:26:40.480
I'm Madea!

01:26:40.571 --> 01:26:42.528
There's another charge.

01:26:42.614 --> 01:26:44.776
And another charge.

01:26:44.867 --> 01:26:48.076
- Man down! Man down!
- Another charge. That's six more years.

01:26:48.161 --> 01:26:50.243
Get her off me!

01:26:52.374 --> 01:26:54.911
One, two, three!

01:26:56.920 --> 01:26:58.661
You giving me a mammogram!

01:26:58.755 --> 01:27:00.257
Hell, you ain't going--

01:27:01.842 --> 01:27:03.833
Get in the car, ma'am.
Get in the car.

01:27:03.927 --> 01:27:06.760
Get in the car.

01:27:06.847 --> 01:27:09.839
- Transport chase suspect. Over.
- Affirmative.

01:27:13.437 --> 01:27:15.974
- Stay back, people.
- All right, everybody.

01:27:41.006 --> 01:27:42.622
Just a minute.

01:27:46.637 --> 01:27:49.049
- Hi. How may I help you?
- Yeah, I'm Richard Carney.

01:27:49.139 --> 01:27:51.801
I'm looking for Brenda
and Michael Brown.

01:27:51.892 --> 01:27:55.351
- What about?
- I'm a sports agent and, well, can we talk?

01:27:55.437 --> 01:27:57.724
Uh, what about?
How'd you get my address?

01:27:57.814 --> 01:27:59.851
Ma, Ma, please.

01:28:02.986 --> 01:28:04.602
Come on in.

01:28:06.114 --> 01:28:07.570
Hi.

01:28:07.658 --> 01:28:09.194
- How you doing?
- Good.

01:28:10.577 --> 01:28:12.909
I sent your son's tape
to two professional teams.

01:28:13.914 --> 01:28:15.746
And they were very impressed.

01:28:15.832 --> 01:28:17.243
I've already got two teams

01:28:17.334 --> 01:28:19.746
that are interested
in signing him right now.

01:28:19.836 --> 01:28:21.418
- Really?
- Yes.

01:28:21.505 --> 01:28:23.371
And I can make a really
good deal for your son.

01:28:24.758 --> 01:28:27.250
So what do you want to do?

01:28:27.344 --> 01:28:28.960
Hmm?

01:28:29.054 --> 01:28:30.590
What do you think?

01:28:33.976 --> 01:28:35.512
So what about college?

01:28:35.602 --> 01:28:37.184
We'll have you take
college courses,

01:28:37.270 --> 01:28:39.398
- even help you get a degree.
- Mama...

01:28:45.904 --> 01:28:47.565
Let's do it.

01:28:47.656 --> 01:28:49.488
- Okay. All right.
- Yeah?

01:28:49.574 --> 01:28:52.282
- Mm-hmm.
- Let's do it.

01:28:52.369 --> 01:28:54.235
- Yeah.
- Okay.

01:28:54.329 --> 01:28:57.822
Um, he signed a contract
with someone to be his manager.

01:28:57.916 --> 01:29:00.829
Does that person have any legal grounds
to any of his money?

01:29:00.919 --> 01:29:02.660
- You mean Harry Belton?
- Yeah.

01:29:02.754 --> 01:29:05.872
That contract didn't ask for money.
It was more of a guidance thing.

01:29:05.966 --> 01:29:07.456
He wasn't even trying to get paid.

01:29:07.551 --> 01:29:09.713
I guess with all of his
knowledge of this business,

01:29:09.803 --> 01:29:11.885
he just didn't want him
to be taken advantage of.

01:29:15.559 --> 01:29:17.641
Listen, Miss Brown,

01:29:17.728 --> 01:29:19.344
I'll be in touch in a week, okay?

01:29:19.438 --> 01:29:21.270
And you, young man,

01:29:21.356 --> 01:29:24.064
- you get ready.
- Yes, sir.

01:29:24.151 --> 01:29:28.110
We'd like to say that the Thunderhawks
are very happy to have him on board.

01:29:28.196 --> 01:29:31.154
A million dollars is a lot of money...

01:29:31.241 --> 01:29:34.154
- I'm his daddy.
- ...are other players going to be jealous--

01:29:34.244 --> 01:29:36.155
Hey, son, how you doing?

01:29:36.246 --> 01:29:38.032
Look, son, can I holler
at you a minute?

01:29:38.123 --> 01:29:41.991
- Mama.
- He's still your daddy.

01:29:42.085 --> 01:29:44.702
- What is he to me?
- I just want to say congratulations, boy.

01:29:44.796 --> 01:29:47.003
- I'm proud of you. You did it.
- Hey hey hey.

01:29:47.090 --> 01:29:50.208
When you had the chance to be in my life,
you didn't want no part of me.

01:29:50.302 --> 01:29:52.464
You should have thought
about all this before.

01:29:52.554 --> 01:29:54.670
Hey, now, come on.
Don't be like that.

01:29:54.765 --> 01:29:57.803
I don't know why you here, man.
That $25 an hour is waiting on you.

01:29:57.893 --> 01:29:59.509
What position is he
going to play?

01:29:59.603 --> 01:30:03.096
Coach, what do you think Mike's
gonna do with all the money?

01:30:03.190 --> 01:30:05.397
Why don't we let Mike
answer that question?

01:30:05.484 --> 01:30:08.772
Mike, what are you gonna
do with all that money?

01:30:10.489 --> 01:30:12.025
Make sure my mom and my sisters

01:30:12.115 --> 01:30:14.652
are taken care of.

01:30:14.743 --> 01:30:18.281
- And he's gonna finish school.
- And finish school.

01:30:18.371 --> 01:30:20.408
Hey, Mike, what are you
gonna do for your dad?

01:30:20.499 --> 01:30:22.957
- Who?
- Isn't that your father?

01:30:23.043 --> 01:30:24.533
Well, that's funny.

01:30:24.628 --> 01:30:26.960
I've-- I've seen my father
twice since I was four.

01:30:28.590 --> 01:30:30.046
My mom's been breaking her back

01:30:30.133 --> 01:30:32.591
to make sure my sisters and I

01:30:32.677 --> 01:30:34.338
had food on the table.

01:30:34.429 --> 01:30:36.966
We lived in the projects
while he went on

01:30:37.057 --> 01:30:40.220
and started his life with someone else
living the good life,

01:30:40.310 --> 01:30:43.894
but somehow he seemed
to make it to my big day.

01:30:43.980 --> 01:30:47.439
Why don't I let my dad answer that
for you? Come on, Dad.

01:30:47.526 --> 01:30:49.267
Are you proud of your son?

01:30:49.361 --> 01:30:51.102
What was he like as a kid?

01:30:51.196 --> 01:30:53.107
How were his grades
growing up?

01:30:53.198 --> 01:30:55.860
- Tell us about the moves he got from you.
- Favorite game memory?

01:30:55.951 --> 01:30:57.908
Well, I-- you know,
that was a long time ago.

01:30:57.994 --> 01:31:01.203
He's always been a good boy.
He's always been real athletic

01:31:01.289 --> 01:31:04.077
and-- and he's always
loved his basketball.

01:31:04.167 --> 01:31:05.999
How do you feel
about your son's comments?

01:31:08.213 --> 01:31:09.829
Hey, you-- you know, it--

01:31:11.383 --> 01:31:13.124
you know what?

01:31:13.218 --> 01:31:15.004
Are you gonna spend
more time with him now?

01:31:15.095 --> 01:31:17.086
That's up to my boy.
That's up to Mike.

01:31:17.180 --> 01:31:19.467
- I hope so.
- With you showing up at this time,

01:31:19.558 --> 01:31:22.266
some folks would consider
that gold digging.

01:31:22.352 --> 01:31:24.639
But hey, this is
all about my son, right?

01:31:24.729 --> 01:31:26.311
This is all about
my boy, all right?

01:31:26.398 --> 01:31:28.685
This is not about me.

01:31:40.745 --> 01:31:42.406
This isn't the way home.

01:31:42.497 --> 01:31:44.079
Yeah, I know.

01:31:45.083 --> 01:31:46.824
What?

01:31:48.545 --> 01:31:49.956
Ma, you were wrong about Harry.

01:31:50.046 --> 01:31:52.663
Michael, you don't know
nothing about that, okay?

